text: "Go All the Way" is a 1972 song by Raspberries and is the second single from their debut studio album Raspberries. It was their biggest hit of their career and went to number 5 in the United States and Canada and number 14 in Australia. It was banned by the BBC in the United Kingdom for sexual content. ==References== Category:1972 songs Category:1970s ballads Category:Rock ballads Category:Power pop songs Category:The Killers songs
